nts1.d:
London-based DJ and producer Nabihah Iqbal (formerly known as Throwing Shade) brings you an ethnomusicological perspective on weird and wonderful music from around the world. Expect regular themed special episode; a good dose of history, and above all, good music to broaden your horizons. Every other Tuesday, midday-1pm. You can listen back to previous Throwing Shade episodes here
From the host: "Recorded in Sydney, with Nabihah Iqbal in the first hour & Ben Chiu in the second."
Settle in for weekly shows from Margeaux aka @marg.mp3, soothing with an hour of selections, offering an eclectic range of sounds old and new.

nts1.n: NTS Guide to: Komuso flute - Shakuhachi
nts1.d: The Komuso were a sect of non-monastic wandering Buddhist monks who emerged in Edo period Japan, who were famous for their face-obscuring woven straw basket masks called tengai. They also differed from monastic Monks, who chose to meditate in silence, as the Komuso played a bamboo flute called a shakuhachi as a form of meditation.

Jennifer Walton presents an hour of eclectic picks from research-driven internet crate digging. Following threads of Cosmic Americana, psychedelic timbres and experimental recordings to find through lines between the past and present.

nts1.n: CHANNELING W/ IVAN SMAGGHE & NATHAN GREGORY WILKINS
nts1.d: Old friends and hapless mavericks Ivan Smagghe and Nathan Gregory Wilkins present a fortnightly window into their ramshackle musical world. A show with absolutely no rules (as they'd only break them). We love the unmixable, old & new. We are oddballs and we love you.

Veronica Vasicka presents a monthly 2-hour show featuring the lost synth-wave treasures she has archived from the late 70s and early 80s, along with other iconic underground electronic music drawn from over four decades. Expect to hear exclusive tracks from releases on her seminal Minimal Wave and Cititrax labels plus cassette-only and private press rarities.
Connections in electronic music: the history of house and techno as presented to you by the wonderful Olly Chubb.

nts1.n: MIDNITE MADNESS CCVIV - Fight to Survive
nts1.d: Midnite Madness endeavours to unearth the spirit of the ancient metal gods as well as the genre's new flesh, taking in most styles—heavy, thrash, black, speed, death, punk, doom, etc. There will be some exclusion: no nu-metal, no triggered drums, no posers and no requests. Only metal is real!

Artist and audio maker, Alicia Matthews, takes over the NTS airwaves once a month for a rhythm ’n’ gloom showdown.
Past projects include SUE ZUKI (Domestic Exile/ NTS), LAPS (MIC Records/ DFA Records) and Organs of  Love (Optimo Music).

All flavours of acoustic & historical nuggets from Andras - Melbourne production wiz, composer & sleuth of musical ephemera…
From the host: "bbq boat"

nts2.d:
Into a new sonic universe, blending tropical ambient soundscapes with dancehall and hip hop in a regular hour from Gustavio Koslowski.
From the host: "Vannila Glint first episode welcomes french producer and artist Yuri Online into a new sonic universe, blending tropical ambient soundscapes with dancehall and hip hop in a regular hour shared with Host Gustavio Koslowski."
Skinny Girl Diet are London's foremost riot grrrl duo. Delilah Holliday and Ursula Holliday. Post-punk, glam, garage and all things nice… or something like that.

An exploration of sounds from an expanse of US and east Asian independent rock, all connected by Seam and Bitch Magnet founder, Korean-American musician Soo Young Park.
Selected by Smilegoth

nts2.n: NTS x Bershka Next Up! w/ Kaanijo & ledbyher
nts2.d: The first episode of our new Next Up! show with Kaanijo features special guest and UK underground driving force ledbyher. The pair sit down to talk through formative 2016 memories, the moments that shaped their sound, and their current musical favourites, offering a personal look at influences past and present.

nts2.n: THE GREAT AFRICAN DISCO W/ TEMI KOGBE (R)
nts2.d: Lagos based collector and DJ Temi Kogbe traces connections in African popular culture through vinyl.

Curator and DJ Edna Martinez explores the champeta, an underground musical genre and dance that originated in the Caribbean coast of Colombia in the early 1980s. The rhythms and influences are said to have arrived with the sailors from West Africa in the 1960s and 70s. We will get to know in each episode its specificities and the relevance of this scene.
From the host: "A tribute to a legendary Cartagena picó El Parrandero since 1978, championing soca and Caribbean rhythms. The pure euphoria of Colombian caribbean sound system culture."

Memphis selector and radio host Nya presents an hour of rare soul, boogie, gospel, and funk records once a month.
Artwork by Abby Shoaf

Kumbias mezcladas como nunca antes by hellotones.. direct from the Poblano Mexicano diaspora in New York City and stamping the moment that is the PueblaYork renaissance. Paying homage with mixes blending the sounds of yesteryears’ cumbia labels and the sounds of the future in cumbia happening now.
Joshua Chuquimia Crampton shares an hour of selections, following the release of new record Anata. Playing salay, huayño, charangueadas, J-pop and more.

French vocalist & songwriter Isabelle Antena initially found success as a member of Antena, famous for birthing a quietly influential electro bossa nova sound on their debut "Camino Del Sol". Isabelle further explored latin styles including samba in her solo career, which continued into the early 2000s. Her work has remained a favourite of DJs whose selections skew relaxed and sunny, with Antena and solo tracks continually surfacing on compilations and remix albums. 
This In Focus is an hour exploring the best of Isabelle Antena, created by Pepsi of Bruits de la Passion.

When the world crumbled, and swallowed us whole, the only vibration that remained was The Monolith. Signals from times of past, present and future absorb us and and give us strength to carry on. These are sounds of creation & destruction presented to you by PBDY. 
http://wearetar.com/

ASHTREJINKINS flies the flag for NTS Los Angeles. Tune in for a round-about journey of lo-fi, gritty and experimental beats and productions.
From the host: "100% AshTreJinkins with some unreleased joints in there"

NTS Guide to: Italian Library, Soundtracks and OSTS

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

subtle.n: Out of Phase With Sam Ling

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

subtle.n: Dun Roamin w/ Tomi From Brockley

subtle.d:
Midlands born, London based producer and DJ influenced by UK funky, broken techno, garage and early dubstep. 

Has released on Keysound recordings, RKS, eatmybeat, ec2a, Durkle Disco and Dimsum records

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.

subtle.n: BASICS RECORDS: L MAJOR, TAMEN & SIDESHOW

subtle.d: Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
